# Authentication & Authorization with Clerk

All authentication is handled by [Clerk](https://clerk.com/). Users must **only** be able to access their own data — never another user's.

## Getting the Current User

Always retrieve the authenticated user via Clerk's server helpers. Never trust user-supplied IDs from request bodies or query params as the source of truth for ownership.

This app has **no dedicated sign-in page**. The homepage (`/`) is where sign-in and sign-up buttons are displayed. When an unauthenticated user tries to access a protected page, **always redirect to `/`** — never to `/sign-in` or any other auth route.

```ts
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";
import { redirect } from "next/navigation";

const { userId } = await auth();
if (!userId) {
  redirect("/");
}
```

## Enforcing Data Ownership

Always filter database queries by the authenticated `userId`. Never fetch a resource by ID alone — always scope it to the current user.

```ts
// ❌ BAD — fetches any deck regardless of owner
const deck = await db.query.decksTable.findFirst({
  where: eq(decksTable.id, deckId),
});

// ✅ GOOD — scoped to the authenticated user
const deck = await db.query.decksTable.findFirst({
  where: and(eq(decksTable.id, deckId), eq(decksTable.userId, userId)),
});
```

## Rules

- **Always** call `auth()` at the start of every API route or server action that accesses data.
- **Always** redirect to `/` if `userId` is `null`. Never return a `401` response or redirect to a sign-in page — the app has no sign-in page.
- **Always** include `eq(table.userId, userId)` in queries on user-owned tables (`decksTable`).
- **Never** expose another user's data, even partially (e.g., do not leak IDs or counts).
- For resources owned indirectly (e.g., `cardsTable` via `decksTable`), verify ownership by joining or pre-fetching the parent deck scoped to `userId`.

## Indirect Ownership (Cards)

Cards belong to decks, not directly to users. Always verify the parent deck belongs to the user before accessing its cards.

```ts
const deck = await db.query.decksTable.findFirst({
  where: and(eq(decksTable.id, deckId), eq(decksTable.userId, userId)),
  with: { cards: true },
});
if (!deck) return new Response("Not Found", { status: 404 });
```
